"""
RadioML Modulation Classifier — v7 (RML2018.01a Edition)
==========================================================
Same architecture as v7 (2016 edition) — SNR-adaptive cross-attention
fusion + HOC branch — adapted for RML2018.01a.

OOM FIX (v7_2018 r2)
──────────────────────
  Original error: OOM allocating [64,4,1024,1024] attention matrix.
  CrossStreamAttention over 1024 timesteps = 1024×1024 = 1M entries per
  head per sample. At batch=64, 4 heads, float32 = ~1GB per attention layer.

  Fix: Move sequence compression BEFORE cross-attention.
  CrossAttn now operates on 128 timesteps → 128×128 = 16K entries.
  That's 64x less memory — fits comfortably on GPU.

  New architecture flow:
    Input (B, 1024, 2)
    → CV/Real ResBlocks ×3           (B, 1024, C)
    → StridedConv(stride=8)          (B, 128,  C)   ← compress FIRST
    → CrossStreamAttention ×3        (B, 128,  C)   ← then cross-attn
    → SNR-Adaptive Gate              (B, 128, 160)
    → BiLSTM(128)                    (B, 128, 256)
    → ChannelAttention + GAP         (B, 256)
    → HOC MLP                        (B, 64)
    → Concat + Dense → softmax       (B, 24)

KEY DIFFERENCES FROM 2016 EDITION
───────────────────────────────────
  Dataset:   HDF5 format, arrays X/Y/Z
  Classes:   24 (not 11)
  Seq len:   1024 IQ samples (not 128)
  SNR range: -20 to +30 dB in 2dB steps (26 levels)
  Samples:   4096 per (class, SNR)

SOTA REFERENCE (RML2018.01a)
──────────────────────────────
  MoE-AMC (2023)                        : 71.76% all-SNR average
  Multiscale + HOC (ScienceDirect 2023) : 94.39% high-SNR avg
  Our target                            : >70% all-SNR, >93% high-SNR
"""

